author: CNET
description:
This generation of the 14-inch MacBook Pro is identical to the 2024 model (prices remain unchanged as well) with a single exception — it incorporates the M5 processor.

So far, our testing shows the chip's upgraded GPU architecture delivers big performance improvements over the M4 in the narrow areas where it applies, namely GPU processing for AI and ray traced graphics, along with Apple's typical generation-over-generation performance improvements. 

Unbox the M5 MacBook Pro with us in Space Black. #unboxing #apple #macbookpro #mac #laptop #macbook
title: Unboxing Apple’s 14-Inch M5 MacBook Pro with the Nano-Texture Display 💻

author: CNET
description:
The M5 iPad Pro is basically the same as the M4 model last year, but with a new M5 processor. Apple also claims it has faster 5G wireless and Wi-Fi 7/Bluetooth 6 via new CX1 and N1 modem and wireless chips. (The M4 Pro had Wi-Fi 6E and Bluetooth 5.3). The size, thickness and weight are the same, as are Pencil Pro compatibility, cameras and price. Unbox Apple's $2,099 13-inch 1TB
iPad Pro with us #ipadpro #unboxing #apple #m5 #tablet
title: Unboxing Apple’s New $2,100 M5 iPad Pro

author: CNET
description:
Honor’s Magic8 Pro is coming to China first. 

The Magic 8 Pro will be one of the first phones to feature Qualcomm's latest Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5 chip, alongside a 7,200-mAh silicon-carbon battery with 120-watt SuperCharge and an AI-driven telephoto camera system. But the global version may have different specs in regards to battery and charging. Let’s unbox the Honor Magic 8 Pro 📲 #unboxing #honor #honormagic8pro #smartphone #tech
title: Unboxing the New Honor Magic 8 Pro 📲
